<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Buck</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that the registration as superficies of titles to
                            perpetual leases is not acceptable to this Government without some
                            authoritative interpretation of the Japanese Government that title under
                            that style is not inferior to that of the perpetual lease; and that, so
                            far as advised, this Government is not prepared to concede that
                            buildings on perpetual leases are subject to taxation not specified in
                            original lease.</p>
                        <p>Instructions sent by mail.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>